If you have the money to pick up standard dumbbell plates, the best improvised handle money can buy is a length of 3/4" iron pipe.
A 12" length will allow you to make up near any low to mid-weight dumbbell, and an 18" length is perfect for rows.
Get yourself a few real shaft collars (which are going to be the majority of the cost if you take that route) or get a few of those two-piece pipe holders. You'll need four per dumbbell, and the shaft collars are better in the sense that once properly tightened, they will hold a few hundred pounds against gravity.
You might only use them for a few things, but heavy weight done carefully and in low reps will improve your soft tissue strength. Muscles now are good, but the ability to move properly twenty or forty years later is kind.

Look at everything around you. The world is your gym if you just push against it the right way.
